myNumMissing

protected double myNumMissing
Used to count the number of missing data points presented When a data point having the value of Double.NaN is presented it is excluded from the summary statistics and the number of missing points is noted. Implementers of subclasses are responsible for properly collecting this value and resetting this value.

getConfidenceCoefficient

public double getConfidenceCoefficient()
Gets the confidence interval coefficient. The default is given by AbstractStatistic.DEFAULT_CONFIDENCE_COEFF = 1.965, which is a 95% confidence level assuming normally distributed data.

Specified by:
getConfidenceCoefficient in interface StatisticAccessorIfc
Returns:
A double representing the coefficient

getNumberMissing

public double getNumberMissing()
Description copied from interface: StatisticAccessorIfc
When a data point having the value of Double.NaN is presented it is excluded from the summary statistics and the number of missing points is noted. This method reports the number of missing points that occurred during the collection
